<a name="2716"></a>

<div class="sponsorshipTitle">Day 24</div>

<STRONG>Schlage LiNK by Ingersoll Rand Security Technologies:&nbsp;Unlock Doors for Friends Remotely<BR></STRONG><IMG height=160 hspace=8 src="/print/images/photos/SchlageLiNK_sm.jpg" width=134 align=left vspace=5>Ingersoll Rand Security Technologies is a leading global provider of products and services that make environments safe, secure and productive. The Schlage LiNK System from Ingersoll Rand Security Technologies utilizes a web-based design to allow users to unlock doors using a mobile phone or computer. <BR><BR>It is the first and only wireless-controlled and Z-Wave enabled door lock, giving homeowners the power to remotely control and monitor access to their home and their Z-Wave enabled home automation devices 24/7. <BR><BR>Using any web-enabled computer, mobile phone or PDA, homeowners can grant immediate access to family, friends and even service providers using the Schlage LiNK online portal or mobile phone application.<BR><BR>The product will be on display at the 2009 International CES in the LVCC, South Hall 1, Booth #20350.

