<a name="2653"></a>

<div class="sponsorshipTitle">Day 30</div>

<H4>Chumby: Cuddly<EM> and</EM> Functional</H4><A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5667481/Chumby-Industries-Inc-/Details.aspx"><IMG height=69 hspace=8 src="/print/images/content/chumby_logo_text90.gif" width=239 align=left border=0></A><BR>Our first day on the Countdown to CES allows us to highlight a new CES exhibitor that shows technology can be both functional and cuddly.<BR><BR>Every once in a while, a CE product comes along with the right combination of innovation and fun that simply makes people smile, and <A href="http://www.chumby.com/" target=_blank>Chumby</A> definitely has that power. <A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5667481/Chumby-Industries-Inc-/Details.aspx">Chumby</A> takes the best of the Internet and puts it into a soft, playful and (dare&nbsp;we s<IMG height=134 hspace=8 src="/print/images/photos/chlatte_174x162.jpg" width=172 align=right vspace=5>ay) cute little package. Music, sports scores, weather, news, gaming and messaging are all among the over 1,000 different widgets that <A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5667481/Chumby-Industries-Inc-/Details.aspx">Chumby</A> makes available.<BR><BR>This squeezable Internet tool is Wi-Fi enabled and costs less than $200.&nbsp;It is the ultimate push-pull Internet device — you tell <A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5667481/Chumby-Industries-Inc-/Details.aspx">Chumby</A> what information you want, and it finds it on the Internet automatically for you and updates itself constantly. <A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5667481/Chumby-Industries-Inc-/Details.aspx">Chumby</A> can even become an Internet radio through Pandora.&nbsp;To keep itself fresh, <A href="http://myces.bdmetrics.com/CDT-5667481/Chumby-Industries-Inc-/Details.aspx">Chumby</A> has a Linux-based, open-source platform that is open to developers who want to improve the product with cool new widgets — exactly the kind of spirit of entrepreneurship that keeps our industry humming.

